{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ukb5CiafaW6VmFSv7UZuCF","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 2.3: Default Embedded Workflow\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want a default workflow YAML shipped with codeharness at `templates/workflows/default.yaml`,\n11\tso that `codeharness run` works out of the box without requiring custom workflow configuration.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** codeharness is installed\n16\t   **When** `templates/workflows/default.yaml` is inspected\n17\t   **Then** the file exists and contains a valid YAML document with `tasks` and `flow` top-level keys\n18\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n19\t\n20\t2. **Given** the default workflow defines tasks\n21\t   **When** the `tasks` section is inspected\n22\t   **Then** it defines at least three tasks: `implement` (agent: dev, scope: per-story, session: fresh, source_access: true), `verify` (agent: evaluator, scope: per-run, session: fresh, source_access: false), and `retry` (agent: dev, scope: per-story, session: fresh, source_access: true)\n23\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t3. **Given** the default workflow defines a flow\n26\t   **When** the `flow` section is inspected\n27\t   **Then** the flow order is: `implement`, `verify`, then a `loop:` block containing `[retry, verify]`\n28\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n29\t\n30\t4. **Given** the default workflow YAML file\n31\t   **When** validated against the workflow JSON schema at `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json` using `parseWorkflow()`\n32\t   **Then** it passes validation with no errors and returns a typed `ResolvedWorkflow` object\n33\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t5. **Given** the `verify` task in the default workflow\n36\t   **When** its properties are inspected\n37\t   **Then** `source_access` is `false` and `scope` is `per-run`, enforcing blind evaluation of the final artifact\n38\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n39\t\n40\t6. **Given** the `retry` task in the default workflow\n41\t   **When** its properties are inspected\n42\t   **Then** it has `source_access: true` and `scope: per-story`, so the dev agent can fix only failing stories with full source access\n43\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n44\t\n45\t7. **Given** the `templates/workflows/` directory\n46\t   **When** `package.json` `files` array is inspected\n47\t   **Then** `templates/workflows/` is included, ensuring the default workflow ships in the npm package\n48\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n49\t\n50\t8. **Given** unit tests for the default embedded workflow\n51\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n52\t   **Then** all tests pass with 80%+ coverage on the test file, covering: file existence, schema validation via `parseWorkflow()`, task property assertions, flow structure assertions\n53\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n54\t\n55\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n56\t\n57\t- [x] Task 1: Create the default workflow YAML (AC: #1, #2, #3, #5, #6)\n58\t  - [x] Create directory `templates/workflows/`\n59\t  - [x] Create `templates/workflows/default.yaml` with `implement`, `verify`, and `retry` tasks\n60\t  - [x] Set `implement` task: `agent: dev`, `scope: per-story`, `session: fresh`, `source_access: true`\n61\t  - [x] Set `verify` task: `agent: evaluator`, `scope: per-run`, `session: fresh`, `source_access: false`\n62\t  - [x] Set `retry` task: `agent: dev`, `scope: per-story`, `session: fresh`, `source_access: true`\n63\t  - [x] Set flow: `[implement, verify, {loop: [retry, verify]}]`\n64\t\n65\t- [x] Task 2: Update package.json for npm distribution (AC: #7)\n66\t  - [x] Add `\"templates/workflows/\"` to the `files` array in `package.json`\n67\t\n68\t- [x] Task 3: Write unit tests (AC: #4, #8)\n69\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/__tests__/default-workflow.test.ts`\n70\t  - [x] Test: `templates/workflows/default.yaml` exists on disk\n71\t  - [x] Test: `parseWorkflow()` succeeds on the default workflow (schema validation + referential integrity)\n72\t  - [x] Test: returned `ResolvedWorkflow` has `implement`, `verify`, `retry` tasks with correct properties\n73\t  - [x] Test: flow structure is `[implement, verify, {loop: [retry, verify]}]`\n74\t  - [x] Test: `verify` task has `source_access: false` and `scope: per-run`\n75\t  - [x] Test: `retry` task has `source_access: true` and `scope: per-story`\n76\t  - [x] Target 80%+ coverage\n77\t\n78\t## Dev Notes\n79\t\n80\t### Module Location and Architecture Role\n81\t\n82\tThis story creates a static YAML file, not a TypeScript module. The file lives at `templates/workflows/default.yaml` per architecture AD3 (Embedded Template Storage). It is consumed by:\n83\t- `parseWorkflow()` from `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` (story 2.2) at runtime\n84\t- `codeharness init` (story 2.4) which will copy it to `.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml` in the user's project\n85\t- `codeharness run` (story 5.1) which will load the resolved workflow for engine execution\n86\t\n87\t### Default Workflow Design (from PRD and Architecture)\n88\t\n89\tFR6 states: \"System ships a default embedded workflow that handles standard BMAD sprint execution without user customization.\"\n90\t\n91\tThe flow is: implement -> verify -> loop: [retry, verify]. This maps directly to the BMAD sprint execution lifecycle:\n92\t1. **implement** (per-story, dev agent): Dev agent implements each story\n93\t2. **verify** (per-run, evaluator agent): Blind evaluator exercises the final artifact\n94\t3. **loop: [retry, verify]**: If evaluator fails stories, dev retries only failing ones, then evaluator re-verifies from scratch. Loop repeats until all pass or circuit breaker triggers.\n95\t\n96\tThe `verify` task uses `source_access: false` and `scope: per-run` — this enforces the blind evaluator pattern (AD2). The evaluator never sees source code and runs once against the entire artifact (not per-story).\n97\t\n98\t### Established Patterns from Previous Stories\n99\t\n100\tFrom story 2.2 (`workflow-parser.ts`):\n101\t- `parseWorkflow(filePath)` reads YAML, validates against schema, checks referential integrity, returns `ResolvedWorkflow`\n102\t- Import: `import { parseWorkflow } from './workflow-parser.js'`\n103\t- The parser applies defaults (`scope: 'per-story'`, `session: 'fresh'`, `source_access: true`) when fields are omitted\n104\t\n105\tFrom story 2.1 (`workflow.schema.json`):\n106\t- Schema at `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json`\n107\t- Required top-level keys: `tasks`, `flow`\n108\t- Tasks require `agent` field; `scope`, `session`, `source_access` have defaults\n109\t- Flow items are either strings (task references) or objects with `loop:` arrays\n110\t\n111\t### YAML Key Convention\n112\t\n113\tAll keys use `snake_case` per architecture convention: `source_access`, `prompt_template`, `max_budget_usd`, `input_contract`, `output_contract`.\n114\t\n115\t### Package Distribution\n116\t\n117\tThe `templates/workflows/` directory must be added to `package.json` `files` array so it ships in the npm tarball. Existing pattern: `templates/dockerfiles/`, `templates/compose/`, `templates/prompts/`, `templates/docs/`, `templates/otlp/` are already in the `files` array.\n118\t\n119\t### Test Approach\n120\t\n121\tTests should use `parseWorkflow()` to validate the YAML against the real schema. This provides true end-to-end validation: file exists -> YAML parses -> schema validates -> referential integrity passes -> typed result is correct. Use `path.resolve(__dirname, '../../../templates/workflows/default.yaml')` (or equivalent) to locate the file from the test directory. See `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-parser.test.ts` for patterns.\n122\t\n123\t### What This Story Does NOT Do\n124\t\n125\t- **Does not create the `codeharness init` command** that copies the workflow to the project (story 2.4)\n126\t- **Does not create any agent YAML files** (story 3.2)\n127\t- **Does not implement flow execution** (story 5.1)\n128\t- **Does not implement workflow patching** (story 9.1)\n129\t- **Does not add `prompt_template` fields** to tasks — those are optional and will be configured per-project or in agent YAML\n130\t\n131\t### Architecture Constraints\n132\t\n133\t- **File location:** `templates/workflows/default.yaml` per AD3\n134\t- **YAML key convention:** `snake_case` per architecture\n135\t- **Schema compliance:** Must pass `src/schemas/workflow.schema.json` validation\n136\t- **No TypeScript code in this file** — it's a static YAML template\n137\t- **No new npm dependencies needed**\n138\t\n139\t### Downstream Consumers\n140\t\n141\t- **Story 2.4 (init command):** Will copy `default.yaml` to `.codeharness/workflows/` during project initialization\n142\t- **Story 5.1 (flow execution):** Will load the workflow via `parseWorkflow()` and execute it\n143\t- **Story 9.1 (workflow patching):** Will use `default.yaml` as the base for `extends: embedded://default` patches\n144\t\n145\t### Project Structure Notes\n146\t\n147\t- New directory: `templates/workflows/`\n148\t- New file: `templates/workflows/default.yaml`\n149\t- New file: `src/lib/__tests__/default-workflow.test.ts`\n150\t- Modified file: `package.json` (add `templates/workflows/` to `files` array)\n151\t- No changes to existing TypeScript source files\n152\t\n153\t### References\n154\t\n155\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 2.3: Default Embedded Workflow]\n156\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD3: Embedded Template Storage]\n157\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Project Structure & Boundaries -- templates/workflows/]\n158\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR6]\n159\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/2-2-workflow-parser-module.md -- parseWorkflow API, ResolvedWorkflow types]\n160\t\n161\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n162\t## Verification Requirements\n163\t\n164\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/2-3-default-embedded-workflow-proof.md)\n165\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n166\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (80%)\n167\t\n168\t## Documentation Requirements\n169\t\n170\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n171\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/2-3-default-embedded-workflow.md\n172\t\n173\t## Testing Requirements\n174\t\n175\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n176\t- [ ] Coverage target: 80%\n177\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n178\t\n179\t## Dev Agent Record\n180\t\n181\t### Agent Model Used\n182\t\n183\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n184\t\n185\t### Debug Log References\n186\t\n187\tN/A — no debug issues encountered.\n188\t\n189\t### Completion Notes List\n190\t\n191\t- Created `templates/workflows/default.yaml` with three tasks (implement, verify, retry) and flow: implement -> verify -> loop:[retry, verify]\n192\t- verify task enforces blind evaluator pattern: source_access=false, scope=per-run\n193\t- retry task allows dev agent to fix failures: source_access=true, scope=per-story\n194\t- Added `templates/workflows/` to package.json files array for npm distribution\n195\t- Created 7 unit tests covering file existence, schema validation via parseWorkflow(), task property assertions, and flow structure\n196\t- All 146 test files pass (3607 tests total), zero regressions\n197\t- Lint passes clean\n198\t\n199\t### Change Log\n200\t\n201\t- 2026-04-02: Implemented story 2-3 — default embedded workflow YAML, package.json update, unit tests\n202\t\n203\t### File List\n204\t\n205\t- templates/workflows/default.yaml (new)\n206\t- src/lib/__tests__/default-workflow.test.ts (new)\n207\t- package.json (modified — added templates/workflows/ to files array)\n208\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017yeHkU1PuPSZdAjtPbsbrV","session_id":"5e9a7eca-0e0b-47b2-8610-117311a6629c","uuid":"d3fb12fc-3403-4c13-91ed-5a8ab5617bb2","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:27:24.584Z"}
