{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011YULfpKASeFxXYhuJfXPSM","type":"tool_result","content":"122\t### AD3: Embedded Template Storage\n123\t\n124\t**Decision:** `templates/` directory in the npm package.\n125\t\n126\t```\n127\ttemplates/\n128\t  agents/\n129\t    dev.yaml\n130\t    qa.yaml\n131\t    architect.yaml\n132\t    pm.yaml\n133\t    sm.yaml\n134\t    analyst.yaml\n135\t    ux-designer.yaml\n136\t    tech-writer.yaml\n137\t    evaluator.yaml\n138\t  workflows/\n139\t    default.yaml\n140\t```\n141\t\n142\tIncluded via `package.json` `files` array. Readable, editable for debugging, consistent with existing pattern (`templates/Dockerfile.verify`).\n143\t\n144\t**Rationale:** Files over compiled strings. Easier to inspect, diff, and debug. The `codeharness init` command copies the default workflow to the project; embedded agents are resolved at runtime from the package location.\n145\t\n146\t### AD4: Config Resolution Caching\n147\t\n148\t**Decision:** Resolve all configs once at engine startup, cache in memory.\n149\t\n150\tOn `codeharness run`:\n151\t1. Resolve workflow: load embedded → apply user patch → apply project patch → cache"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017yeHkU1PuPSZdAjtPbsbrV","session_id":"5e9a7eca-0e0b-47b2-8610-117311a6629c","uuid":"0be5b20a-431c-427d-9863-a40cde9178c9","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:28:16.270Z"}
