erts file exists and content matches `templates/workflows/default.yaml`\n\n---\n\n## AC 2: Existing workflow NOT overwritten without `--force`\n\n**Verified: PASS**\n\n- `init-project.ts` line 97-99: `if (existsSync(workflowDest) && !force)` branch sets `result.workflow = { status: 'exists', ... }` and logs info\n- Test `preserves existing workflow file without --force` passes — pre-creates file with `custom-content`, runs init, asserts content unchanged and status is `exists`\n\n---\n\n## AC 3: Existing workflow IS overwritten with `--force`\n\n**Verified: PASS**\n\n- `init-project.ts` line 100-105: else branch calls `copyFileSync` and sets status to `overwritten` when `overwriting` is true\n- Test `overwrites existing workflow file with --force` passes — pre-creates file, runs init with `force: true`, asserts content matches template and status is `overwritten`\n- Re-run test `overwrites workflow file on re-run with --force` also passes\n\n---\n\n## AC 4: `--force` appears in `codeharness init --help`\n\n**Verified: PASS**\n\n- `src/commands/init.ts` line 37: `.option('--force', 'Overwrite existing generated files', false)`\n- Commander.js auto-includes registered options in `--help` output\n\n---\n\n## AC 5: Success/info messages in console output\n\n**Verified: PASS**\n\n- `init-project.ts` line 99: `info('Workflow: .codeharness/workflows/default.yaml already exists')` for exists case\n- `init-project.ts` line 105: `okOutput('Workflow: .codeharness/workflows/default.yaml created')` for created case\n- `okOutput('Workflow: .codeharness/workflows/default.yaml overwritten')` for overwrite case\n- Messages match AC specification exactly\n\n---\n\n## AC 6: Stack detection — no regressions\n\n**Verified: PASS**\n\n- Test `stack detection still works with workflow generation` passes — asserts stack detection works AND workflow was created\n- All 25 original init-project tests still pass (33 total = 25 original + 8 new)\n\n---\n\n## AC 7: `--json` output includes `workflow` field\n\n**Verified: PASS**\n\n- `src/modules/infra/types.ts` line 81: `workflow?: { status: 'created' | 'exists' | 'overwritten'; path: string };`\n- Test `includes workflow field in --json output` passes — asserts `result.data.workflow` is defined with `status: 'created'` and `path: '.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml'`\n\n---\n\n## AC 8: Unit tests pass covering all scenarios\n\n**Verified: PASS**\n\n- 8 new workflow tests in `init-project.test.ts`:\n  1. `creates .codeharness/workflows/default.yaml on fresh init`\n  2. `preserves existing workflow file without --force`\n  3. `overwrites existing workflow file with --force`\n  4. `includes workflow field in --json output`\n  5. `stack detection still works with workflow generation`\n  6. `overwrites workflow file on re-run with --force`\n  7. `creates workflow file on re-run when missing`\n  8. `preserves workflow file on re-run without --force`\n- 33/33 init-project tests pass, 0 regressions\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| AC | Description | Result |\n|----|-------------|--------|\n| 1 | Fresh init creates workflow from template | PASS |\n| 2 | Existing workflow preserved without --force | PASS |\n| 3 | Existing workflow overwritten with --force | PASS |\n| 4 | --force in help output | PASS |\n| 5 | Success/info console messages | PASS |\n| 6 | Stack detection no regressions | PASS |\n| 7 | --json includes workflow field | PASS |\n| 8 | Unit tests cover all scenarios | PASS |\n\n**Final Result: ALL_PASS (8/8 ACs)**\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":618,"cache_read_input_tokens":36734,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":618,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MsPxtSQKH9QDRZjdWrSdbz","session_id":"5e9a7eca-0e0b-47b2-8610-117311a6629c","uuid":"7af70ccd-9d98-4599-9e3