{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014McR4Y4348qmscFYRGt2dU","type":"tool_result","content":"99\t| **Total** | | **233** | |\n100\t\n101\t### Token Waste Hotspots\n102\t\n103\t1. **`run.test.ts` read 4 times** at different offsets during 1-2 dev — file was too large for single read.\n104\t2. **Test suite run 3 times** during 1-2 dev — first two runs caught missed references.\n105\t3. **`git diff --stat HEAD~1` run twice** during 1-2 verification — redundant.\n106\t4. **1-1 dev had 2 unnecessary test re-runs** due to missed beads references in first pass.\n107\t5. **`npm run test:unit` output at ~600 lines** in 1-2 dev — largest single Bash output of the day. Should pipe through `tail` or `--silent`.\n108\t\n109\t---\n110\t\n111\t## What Went Well\n112\t\n113\t1. **Both deletion stories completed successfully.** 1-1 (beads) and 1-2 (ralph/hooks/legacy) are done. The codebase is now free of both beads and ralph dependencies.\n114\t2. **Code review caught real bugs.** The review phases found HIGH-severity issues (incomplete ralph deletion, broken stats.ts path, dead type members) that would have been shipped without review.\n115\t3. **Coverage held above floor.** 96.78% overall, all 147 remaining files above the 80% per-file minimum.\n116\t4. **Create-story risk predictions were accurate.** Both stories correctly predicted the `src/lib/state.ts` dependency problem and the scope of changes needed.\n117\t5. **Net LOC strongly negative.** -656,265 lines removed (mostly ralph/logs), achieving NFR17's code-reduction goal.\n118\t6. **Verification was fast.** Both stories passed verification on first attempt after code review fixes.\n119\t\n120\t---\n121\t\n122\t## What Went Wrong\n123\t\n124\t1. **Story spec had incorrect file path.** `src/templates/ralph-prompt.ts` vs actual `src/lib/agents/ralph-prompt.ts` — spec was written from memory, not verified.\n125\t2. **Story spec listed `src/lib/state.ts` for deletion** despite 14+ active importers. Dev agent had to make a judgment call to skip it. This could have caused a catastrophic build failure if followed blindly.\n126\t3. **Multiple commands are now stubs/no-ops.** `run`, `applyAllPatches`, `createProofDocument`, `getDriver` — these are by design (Epic 5 rebuilds them), but it means the CLI is partially non-functional until then.\n127\t4. **`codeharness stats` is broken.** Deleting ralph/session-logs means the stats command can no longer find historical data. No cost report can be generated.\n128\t5. **Proof document format mismatch.** Verification had to rewrite the proof to match expected `## AC N: Title` format — the dev/review phases should produce proofs in the correct format.\n129\t\n130\t---\n131\t\n132\t## Lessons Learned\n133\t\n134\t### Patterns to Repeat\n135\t\n136\t- **Create-story risk identification works.** Both stories flagged the real problems before dev started. Keep using the risk analysis step.\n137\t- **Code review as a separate phase catches real issues.** The HIGH-severity ralph directory cleanup miss and the stats.ts broken path were both caught here, not in dev.\n138\t- **Pure-deletion stories with `test-provable` ACs are efficient.** Both stories moved quickly because the acceptance criteria were binary (code exists or it doesn't).\n139\t\n140\t### Patterns to Avoid\n141\t\n142\t- **Story specs listing files for deletion without verifying import count.** Always run `grep -r \"from.*module\"` before listing a file for deletion.\n143\t- **Large test file reads at multiple offsets.** `run.test.ts` was read 4 times. Consider splitting large test files or using targeted grep instead.\n144\t- **Running full test suite without `--silent` or `tail`.** 600-line test output is wasteful. Pipe through `tail -20` unless debugging.\n145\t- **Assuming the stats command will work after deleting its data source.** Should have saved stats before deleting ralph.\n146\t\n147\t---\n148\t\n149\t## Action Items\n150\t\n151\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner |\n152\t|---|--------|----------|-------|\n153\t| 1 | Fix `package.json` `files` array — remove stale `ralph/**/*.sh` and `ralph/AGENTS.md` entries | HIGH | Next session |\n154\t| 2 | Fix `codeharness stats` to handle missing session-logs directory gracefully | MEDIUM | Epic 5 or standalone fix |\n155\t| 3 | Add validation to `create-story` skill: verify file deletion targets have zero importers before listing | MEDIUM | Process improvement |\n156\t| 4 | Clean up `describe.skip('importOnboardingEpic — removed')` in `epic-generator.test.ts` | LOW | Tech debt |\n157\t| 5 | Remove `--keep-beads` and `--keep-ralph` CLI flags from teardown command if still present | LOW | Tech debt |\n158\t| 6 | Begin story 1-3-workflow-state-module — next in sprint plan | HIGH | Next session |\n159\t\n160\t---\n161\t\n162\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-02 (Session 2: Story 1-3)\n163\t\n164\t**Generated:** 2026-04-02T11:10 UTC\n165\t\n166\t## 1. Session Summary\n167\t\n168\t**Date:** 2026-04-02\n169\t**Duration:** ~28 minutes (approx 10:40 - 11:08 UTC)\n170\t**Stories attempted:** 1\n171\t**Stories completed:** 1\n172\t**Epic 1 status:** DONE (3/3 stories complete)\n173\t\n174\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Commit |\n175\t|-------|-----------|---------|--------|\n176\t| 1-3-workflow-state-module | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification | done | `39ec40c` |\n177\t\n178\tThis session completed the final story in Epic 1 (v2 Foundation Cleanup). The workflow-state module provides YAML-based persistence for workflow execution state — a building block for Epic 5 (flow execution engine). Epic 1 is now fully closed.\n179\t\n180\t---\n181\t\n182\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n183\t\n184\t### Categorized Issues from Session Log\n185\t\n186\t**Spec/Config Gaps (2)**\n187\t- `workflow.yaml` vs `workflow.md` naming inconsistency in skill trigger configuration.\n188\t- No `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` or `project-context.md` found — create-story agent had to infer context from existing artifacts.\n189\t\n190\t**Code Quality Issues Found by Review (3)**\n191\t- **HIGH:** `readState`/`writeState` naming collision with existing `state.ts` module — renamed to `readWorkflowState`/`writeWorkflowState`. Fixed.\n192\t- **MEDIUM:** `isValidWorkflowState` did not validate `tasks_completed` element shapes, `evaluator_scores`, or `score_history` element types. Fixed — 6 tests added.\n193\t- **LOW (deferred):** Branch coverage at 72.22%, stale AGENTS.md entries from stories 1-1/1-2.\n194\t\n195\t**Test/Coverage Observations (2)**\n196\t- AC #3 \"state survives process exit\" tested via separate function calls, not actual OS process restarts — weaker guarantee but sufficient for unit tests.\n197\t- Statement coverage at 80% meets AC; branch coverage at 73.52% below the 80% aspiration but not a blocker.\n198\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PAev56xh5KBVmmNBmbCvca","session_id":"5e9a7eca-0e0b-47b2-8610-117311a6629c","uuid":"db7c4d2a-e1e5-4498-b89b-68bdea2b1f6b","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:44:36.395Z"}
