{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AgeF6NTJRjZRoVQmJQLTSe","type":"tool_result","content":"760\t| Files above 80% floor | 150/150 |\n761\t\n762\t### Recurring Issues (Unresolved After 4 Sessions)\n763\t\n764\t1. **Verification proof format failures** — caused retry loops in 3 of 4 sessions. Estimated wasted cost: $6-10 across the day.\n765\t2. **`codeharness stats` broken** — no automated cost tracking for 4 sessions.\n766\t3. **`package.json` stale entries** — carried for 3 sessions without fix.\n767\t4. **`_bmad/config.yaml` location confusion** — glob-resolved 4 times.\n768\t\n769\tThese are the top priorities for the next session before starting story 2-3.\n770\t\n771\t---\n772\t\n773\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-02 (Session 5: Story 2-3 Review + Verification)\n774\t\n775\t**Generated:** 2026-04-02T18:10 UTC\n776\t\n777\t## 1. Session Summary\n778\t\n779\t**Date:** 2026-04-02\n780\t**Time budget:** 30 minutes (started 14:08:49 UTC)\n781\t**Stories attempted:** 1\n782\t**Stories completed:** 1\n783\t\n784\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Notes |\n785\t|-------|-----------|---------|-------|\n786\t| 2-3-default-embedded-workflow | code-review, verification | done | Dev work done in prior session; this session did review + verification only |\n787\t\n788\tThis session completed the default embedded workflow story — the third story in Epic 2. The story embeds a default `codeharness.workflow.yaml` in the `templates/workflows/` directory, validates it against the JSON Schema from story 2-1, and exposes a `getDefaultWorkflow()` function that returns the parsed workflow object. All 8 ACs passed test-provable verification on the first attempt. No failures, no retries needed.\n789\t\n790\t**Sprint progress after session:** Epic 2 at 60% (3/5 — stories 2-1, 2-2, 2-3 done). Stories 2-4 and 2-5 remain in backlog.\n791\t\n792\t---\n793\t\n794\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n795\t\n796\t### Categorized Issues from Session Log\n797\t\n798\t**Process Notes (1)**\n799\t- Sprint-status.yaml update skipped per orchestrator instructions — compliant behavior, consistent across all 5 sessions.\n800\t\n801\t**Code Quality Issues (2 — LOW, not fixed)**\n802\t- Tests are integration tests depending on real filesystem and `parseWorkflow()`. No unit-level mocks. Acceptable for a static YAML story.\n803\t- Default workflow YAML has no inline comments explaining design rationale.\n804\t\n805\t**Pre-existing Failures (2)**\n806\t- BATS integration tests emit BW01 warnings for deleted scripts (ralph.sh, onboard.sh, verify_gates.sh, validate_epic_docs.sh). Pre-existing from story 1-2.\n807\t- 5 grep attempts on coverage output returned empty due to ANSI color codes (code-review phase).\n808\t\n809\t**Verification Format Issues (2)**\n810\t- Initial proof failed `codeharness verify` (0/8 ACs) because validator requires `bash` blocks followed by `output` blocks as evidence. Rewrote in expected format.\n811\t- Missing exec-plan warning flagged during verification — not part of verification request but noted.\n812\t\n813\t**Coverage Reporting (1)**\n814\t- Coverage output truncates long filenames, making per-file confirmation harder. Cross-referenced with path to resolve.\n815\t\n816\t### Severity Distribution\n817\t\n818\t| Severity | Count | Fixed? |\n819\t|----------|-------|--------|\n820\t| LOW | 2 | Deferred (test style, YAML comments) |\n821\t| Pre-existing | 2 | Not addressed |\n822\t\n823\tThis was the cleanest session of the day for issues. Zero HIGH or MEDIUM issues found — the implementation was correct as submitted.\n824\t\n825\t---\n826\t\n827\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n828\t\n829\t### Session Cost\n830\t\n831\t`codeharness stats --save` failed — session-logs directory still missing (deleted in story 1-2, never rebuilt). Cost data reconstructed from subagent token reports in `.session-issues.md`.\n832\t\n833\t**Aggregate Tool Usage Across Phases (Story 2-3 — review + verification only):**\n834\t\n835\t| Tool | code-review | verification | Total |\n836\t|------|-------------|--------------|-------|\n837\t| Bash | 11 | 12 | **23** |\n838\t| Read | 6 | 4 | **10** |\n839\t| Edit | 1 | 0 | **1** |\n840\t| Write | 1 | 1 | **2** |\n841\t| Grep | 0 | 1 | **1** |\n842\t| Glob | 1 | 0 | **1** |\n843\t| Skill | 1 | 0 | **1** |\n844\t| **Total** | **21** | **18** | **39** |\n845\t\n846\t**Files Read:** ~11 unique files across session (8 in code-review, 3 in verification).\n847\t\n848\t### Subagent-Level Breakdown\n849\t\n850\t**Code Review (21 calls):** Bash-heavy (11 calls) — ran vitest with coverage, codeharness coverage check, and test suite. 5 grep attempts on ANSI-colored coverage output returned empty — this is the same ANSI parsing problem reported in Sessions 2, 3, and 4. One Edit to fix a minor issue. Found zero bugs — implementation was clean. Cost was low and proportionate.\n851\t\n852\t**Verification (18 calls):** Bash-heavy (12 calls) — `npm test` (~80 lines), `npx vitest --coverage` (~40 lines). Ran npm test twice and multiple coverage commands with different grep patterns due to filename truncation. Proof had to be rewritten once due to format mismatch — but only once (improvement over Session 3's three attempts).\n853\t\n854\t### Token Waste Hotspots\n855\t\n856\t1. **5 empty grep attempts on ANSI coverage output (code-review)** — same issue as Sessions 2-4. `--no-color` flag would eliminate this.\n857\t2. **npm test run twice in verification** — second run was likely a confirmation pass. Minor waste.\n858\t3. **Multiple coverage grep patterns due to filename truncation** — coverage formatter truncates paths, forcing extra pattern attempts.\n859\t4. **Proof format rewrite (1x)** — down from 3x in Session 3. Improvement, but still nonzero waste.\n860\t\n861\t### Estimated Session Cost\n862\t\n863\tUsing the Session 3 rate ($0.13/call): 39 calls x $0.13 = **~$5.07**. This is the cheapest session of the day, which is expected — only 2 phases ran (code-review + verification), and the implementation was pre-done.\n864\t\n865\t### Efficiency Comparison Across All Sessions\n866\t\n867\t| Session | Story | Phases | Total Tool Calls | Calls/Phase | Type |\n868\t|---------|-------|--------|-----------------|-------------|------|\n869\t| 1 | 1-1 + 1-2 | 8 | ~233 | ~29 | Deletion |\n870\t| 2 | 1-3 | 4 | 74 | 18.5 | Greenfield (full) |\n871\t| 3 | 2-1 | 4 | ~86 | ~21.5 | Greenfield (full) |\n872\t| 4 | 2-2 | 4 | 63 | 15.75 | Greenfield (full) |\n873\t| 5 | 2-3 | 2 | 39 | 19.5 | Review + verify only |\n874\t\n875\tSession 5 had only 2 phases but 19.5 calls/phase — slightly higher than Session 4 per-phase (15.75). The code-review phase was call-heavy due to the ANSI grep retries (5 wasted calls out of 21).\n876\t\n877\t### Full-Day Cost Summary (Updated)\n878\t\n879\t| Session | Story(ies) | Tool Calls | Estimated Cost |\n880\t|---------|-----------|-----------|----------------|\n881\t| 1 | 1-1, 1-2 | ~233 | ~$10 |\n882\t| 2 | 1-3 | 74 | ~$5.48 |\n883\t| 3 | 2-1 | ~86 | ~$8.34 |\n884\t| 4 | 2-2 | 63 | ~$8.19 |\n885\t| 5 | 2-3 | 39 | ~$5.07 |\n886\t| Orchestrator overhead | — | ~20 | ~$4-5 |\n887\t| **Full Day Total** | **6 stories** | **~515** | **~$41** |\n888\t\n889\t### Cumulative Sprint Cost\n890\t\n891\t- Historical cumulative: $900.92 (158 stories prior)\n892\t- Today: ~$41\n893\t- **Running total: ~$942**\n894\t- **Average cost per story today: ~$6.83/story** (6 stories at ~$41)\n895\t\n896\t---\n897\t\n898\t## 4. What Went Well\n899\t\n900\t1. **Clean pass on first attempt.** All 8 ACs passed verification with zero failures, zero retries needed. This is the first story of the day with no code-review findings at MEDIUM or higher severity.\n901\t2. **Implementation was correct as submitted.** Code review found no bugs — only LOW-priority style observations. The dev work (from the prior session) was solid.\n902\t3. **Cheapest session of the day.** 39 tool calls, ~$5.07 estimated. Running only review + verification (when dev is already done